{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":666,"text":"One of my favorite words in the whole\nof the Oxford English Dictionary"},{"time":4271,"text":"is \"snollygoster,\""},{"time":6138,"text":"just because it sounds so good."},{"time":7808,"text":"And what snollygoster means\nis \"a dishonest politician.\""},{"time":12116,"text":"Although there was a 19th-century\nnewspaper editor"},{"time":14670,"text":"who defined it rather better when he said,"},{"time":16727,"text":"\"A snollygoster is a fellow\nwho seeks office"},{"time":19267,"text":"regardless of party,\nplatform or principle,"},{"time":22874,"text":"and who, when he wins,"},{"time":24406,"text":"gets there by the sheer force\nof monumental talknophical assumnancy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":29654,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31207,"text":"Now, I have no idea\nwhat \"talknophical\" is."},{"time":33329,"text":"Something to do with words, I assume."},{"time":35155,"text":"But it's very important that words\nare at the center of politics,"},{"time":38454,"text":"and all politicians know\nthey have to try and control language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41683,"text":"It wasn't until, for example, 1771"},{"time":44735,"text":"that the British Parliament\nallowed newspapers to report"},{"time":49182,"text":"the exact words that were said\nin the debating chamber."},{"time":52454,"text":"And this was actually\nall down to the bravery"},{"time":54775,"text":"of a guy with the extraordinary\nname of Brass Crosby,"},{"time":58108,"text":"who took on Parliament."},{"time":59858,"text":"And he was thrown into the Tower of London"},{"time":61960,"text":"and imprisoned,"},{"time":64078,"text":"but he was brave enough,"},{"time":66911,"text":"he was brave enough\nto take them on, and in the end,"},{"time":69414,"text":"he had such popular support\nin London that he won."},{"time":71873,"text":"And it was only a few years later"},{"time":73660,"text":"that we have the first recorded use\nof the phrase \"as bold as brass.\""},{"time":79061,"text":"Most people think\nthat's down to the metal."},{"time":81109,"text":"It's not; it's down to a campaigner\nfor the freedom of the press."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85551,"text":"But to really show you\nhow words and politics interact,"},{"time":89761,"text":"I want to take you back\nto the United States of America,"},{"time":92405,"text":"just after they'd achieved independence."},{"time":95209,"text":"And they had to face the question"},{"time":96981,"text":"of what to call\nGeorge Washington, their leader."},{"time":99710,"text":"They didn't know."},{"time":100990,"text":"What do you call the leader\nof a republican country?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104335,"text":"And this was debated\nin Congress for ages and ages."},{"time":107226,"text":"And there were all sorts\nof suggestions on the table,"},{"time":109782,"text":"which might have made it."},{"time":111001,"text":"I mean, some people\nwanted him to be called"},{"time":113262,"text":"\"Chief Magistrate Washington,\""},{"time":115076,"text":"and other people,\n\"His Highness, George Washington,\""},{"time":117589,"text":"and other people,"},{"time":118847,"text":"\"Protector of the Liberties"},{"time":121629,"text":"of the People of the United States\nof America Washington.\""},{"time":124704,"text":"Not that catchy."},{"time":126347,"text":"Some people just wanted\nto call him king --"},{"time":128805,"text":"it was tried and tested."},{"time":130335,"text":"They weren't even being monarchical,"},{"time":132089,"text":"they had the idea that you could\nbe elected king for a fixed term."},{"time":135327,"text":"And, you know, it could have worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137615,"text":"And everybody got insanely bored,"},{"time":139497,"text":"because this debate\nwent on for three weeks."},{"time":141595,"text":"I read a diary of this poor senator\nwho just keeps coming back,"},{"time":144609,"text":"\"Still on this subject.\""},{"time":145881,"text":"And the reason for the delay\nand the boredom"},{"time":148434,"text":"was that the House of Representatives\nwere against the Senate."},{"time":152073,"text":"The House of Representatives didn't want\nWashington to get drunk on power."},{"time":156314,"text":"They didn't want to call him \"king,\"\nin case that gave him ideas,"},{"time":159425,"text":"or his successor ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160789,"text":"So they wanted to give him\nthe humblest, meagerest,"},{"time":163960,"text":"most pathetic title\nthat they could think of."},{"time":167356,"text":"And that title ..."},{"time":169444,"text":"was \"President.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":170863,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172951,"text":"\"President.\" They didn't invent the title."},{"time":175002,"text":"I mean, it existed before,"},{"time":176348,"text":"but it just meant somebody\nwho presides over a meeting."},{"time":179037,"text":"It was like the foreman of the jury."},{"time":180944,"text":"And it didn't have much more grandeur"},{"time":182804,"text":"than the term \"foreman\" or \"overseer.\""},{"time":184682,"text":"There were occasional presidents\nof little colonial councils"},{"time":187579,"text":"and bits of government,"},{"time":188775,"text":"but it was really a nothing title."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190990,"text":"And that's why the Senate objected to it."},{"time":193024,"text":"They said, \"That's ridiculous!\nYou can't call him 'President.'"},{"time":196797,"text":"This guy has to go and sign treaties\nand meet foreign dignitaries."},{"time":200240,"text":"Who's going to take him seriously\nif he's got a silly little title"},{"time":203819,"text":"like 'President of the United\nStates of America'?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":206484,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207519,"text":"And after three weeks\nof debate, in the end,"},{"time":211287,"text":"the Senate did not cave in."},{"time":215366,"text":"Instead, they agreed to use\nthe title \"President\" for now."},{"time":221056,"text":"But they also wanted\nit absolutely set down"},{"time":223864,"text":"that they didn't agree with it,"},{"time":226969,"text":"from a decent respect for the opinions\nand practice of civilized nations,"},{"time":232442,"text":"whether under republican\nor monarchical forms of government,"},{"time":236270,"text":"whose custom it is to annex,"},{"time":238408,"text":"through the office\nof the Chief Magistrate,"},{"time":240448,"text":"titles of respectability --"},{"time":243252,"text":"not bloody \"President.\""},{"time":245382,"text":"And that, in the intercourse\nwith foreign nations,"},{"time":249010,"text":"the majesty of the people\nof the United States"},{"time":252281,"text":"may not be hazarded\nby an appearance of singularity --"},{"time":256288,"text":"i.e., we don't want to look\nlike bloody weirdos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260485,"text":"Now, you can learn\nthree interesting things from this."},{"time":263114,"text":"First of all -- and this is my favorite --"},{"time":265335,"text":"is that, so far as I've ever\nbeen able to find out,"},{"time":267795,"text":"the Senate has never formally\nendorsed the title of President."},{"time":273091,"text":"Barack Obama, President Obama,\nis there on borrowed time,"},{"time":276034,"text":"just waiting for the Senate\nto spring into action."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279198,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280468,"text":"The second thing you can learn"},{"time":281944,"text":"is that, when a government says\nthat this is a temporary measure --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":285188,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287580,"text":"you can still be waiting 223 years later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292854,"text":"But the third thing you can learn --\nand this is the really important one,"},{"time":296394,"text":"the point I want to leave you on --"},{"time":298142,"text":"is that the title, \"President\nof the United States of America,\""},{"time":302098,"text":"doesn't sound that humble\nat all these days, does it?"},{"time":306244,"text":"Something to do\nwith the slightly over 5,000"},{"time":309467,"text":"nuclear warheads he has at his disposal"},{"time":311741,"text":"and the largest economy in the world"},{"time":313938,"text":"and a fleet of drones\nand all that sort of stuff."},{"time":317537,"text":"Reality and history\nhave endowed that title with grandeur."},{"time":324491,"text":"And so the Senate won in the end."},{"time":326133,"text":"They got their title of respectability."},{"time":328585,"text":"And also, the Senate's other worry,\nthe appearance of singularity --"},{"time":332145,"text":"well, it was a singularity back then."},{"time":334293,"text":"But now, do you know\nhow many nations have a president?"},{"time":337166,"text":"A hundred and forty-seven."},{"time":339512,"text":"All because they want\nto sound like the guy"},{"time":341547,"text":"who's got the 5,000 nuclear warheads, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346155,"text":"And so, in the end, the Senate won"},{"time":349058,"text":"and the House of Representatives lost ..."},{"time":352563,"text":"because nobody's going to feel that humble"},{"time":355103,"text":"when they're told that they are now"},{"time":356814,"text":"the President of the United\nStates of America."},{"time":361243,"text":"And that's the important lesson\nI think you can take away,"},{"time":364033,"text":"and the one I want to leave you with."},{"time":365832,"text":"Politicians try to pick and use words\nto shape and control reality,"},{"time":369650,"text":"but in fact,"},{"time":371332,"text":"reality changes words far more\nthan words can ever change reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377242,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}